-- DaimlerChrysler U.S. sales down 2 percent
-- 
-- Tue Jul 3, 2007 11:13am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/03/us-autos-sales-daimlerchrysler-idUSWNAS525020070703

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - DaimlerChrysler AG DCXGn.DE on Tuesday said its U.S. sales fell 2 percent in June. 

 The German automaker, which is in the process of selling its U.S. unit Chrysler Group, said it sold 202,936 vehicles in June. Sales at Chrysler Group, which consists of Jeep, Dodge and Chrysler brands, fell 1 percent to 183,347 vehicles. Sales at the Mercedes-Benz unit fell 6 percent to 19,589 vehicles. The results were not adjusted for an extra selling day in June 2007.